beneficiaryWithdrawStable(uint256,addres.details: Withdraws the beneficiary's available balance to release (fulfilled with success). Only the manager can withdraw the releaseable pool.

returns.amount: The total amount of deposits for the given payer and service ID
The total amount of accumulated fees for the given service ID
The total amount of refunds authorized for the given payer and service ID

initialize(address).details: set counter to 1 to avoid 0 id

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

returns._0: An array of fulfillment record IDs

registerFulfillment(uint256,(uint256,str.details: The fulfiller registers a fulfillment. We need to verify the amount of the fulfillment is actually available to release. Then we can enrich the result with an auto-incremental unique ID. and the timestamp when the record get inserted. If the fulfillment has failed: - a refund will be authorized for a later withdrawal. If these verifications pass: - add the amount fulfilled to the release pool. - substract the amount from the payer's deposits. - update the FulFillmentRecord to the blockchain.

params.fulfillment: the fulfillment result attached to it.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setFulfillableRegistry(address).details: Only callable by the contract owner

params.fulfillableRegistry_: The address of the fulfillable registry

setManager(address).details: Only callable by the contract owner

params.manager_: The address of the protocol manager

setRouter(address).details: Only callable by the contract owner

params.router_: The address of the protocol router

subtractPoolsAndFees(uint256,address,uin.details: Resets the releaseable pools and accumulated fees for a given service and token.

swapPoolsToStable(uint256,uint256,(addre.details: Swaps both releaseable pool and accumulated fees to stablecoins in a single transaction using an off-chain generated Dex aggregator call.  Requirements: - Only the manager can call this. - A Dex aggregator address must be whitelisted. - The fromToken must have sufficient combined balance.

params.swapData: The struct capturing the aggregator call data, tokens, and amounts.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

withdrawAccumulatedFeesStable(uint256,ad.details: Withdraws the accumulated fees for a given service ID. Only the manager can withdraw the accumulated fees.

withdrawFulfillerPoolAndFees(address,uin.details: Withdraws the fulfiller's pool and fees.

withdrawRefund(uint256,uint256).details: Refund accumulated balance for a refundee, forwarding all gas to the recipient. WARNING: Forwarding all gas opens the door to reentrancy vulnerabilities. Make sure you trust the recipient, or are either following the checks-effects-interactions pattern or using {ReentrancyGuard}.

_stableReleasePools(uint256,address).notice: The mapping of service IDs to their corresponding releaseable pools.

beneficiaryWithdraw(uint256).notice: Withdraws the beneficiary's available balance to release (fulfilled with success).

getNativeFeesFor(uint256).notice: Retrieves the accumulated fees for a given service ID

getRefundsFor(address,uint256).notice: Retrieves the total refunds authorized for a given payer and service ID
